<hr size=1> Spring day, been raining for a few days so clean tarmac. Warming up nicely. New tyres on thursday, done just under 700 miles since, so nicely bedded in. 20 miles of motorway, steady 120mph, engine is smooth, rubber is grippy, long sweep left up slip road onto the beginning of a nice piece of twisty A road. Wind noise finally dropped now speed is sub 100, so turn on minidisc, cool, start with Bonjovi. Enjoying the sunshine, seems forever since this kind of weather. Through a village, low speeds here, but bike is feeling responsive. Life is good.<br>Come through village, back to national speed limit zones, playtime. Still fairly laid back tunes on the headphones, just buzzing along nicely enjoying the ride, onto the straight and an L reg gixer 1100 passes me like I am stood still. OK, got a playmate now. Drop a gear, try to catch it, no chance, damn it. Get into the first set of corners and he comes back into sight, fast in a straight line but doesn't appear to understand corners. Jovi finishes, and here starts the problems, next track is Hatesong, by Cubanate, red mist drops and adrenaline begins. Struggle to overtake this damned suzuki for best part of 5 miles, I can get right up his exhaust on the corners, but the bastard fecks off into the distance on straight aways, even chin on tank I can only scrape 110 on a shortish straight. Come up to a stretch I know well, long straight but the right hand bend isn't too bad although it is signed as a rough turn, hit the front brake as I come to the corner, engine bouncing off front mudguard, but finally outbraked the gixer. Into the first corner, music blaring, go to put knee down, MISTAKE! in work kit, no knee slider, pick up the line, still ahead. Gixer catching, cog down two, engine screams, off again. Finally lose the muppet on the 1100. reach roundabout, Oh shit, coke can on the line, wheels judder as they slide. *sigh of relief* made it. Get to pick up, engine off. Lever sphincter off bike seat (scary coke can moment) and let pulse subside from the 140 mark.<br><br>Sometimes life is good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uaanalleinicefalcon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aanallein Icefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>1st post by this guy</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 11:36:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2702.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: To the bikers out there *longish*</span><hr size=1> You just reminded me why I ride a Harley....<br><br>Cruising at 65, dodging bugs, and setting off car alarms.  Ya gotta love the spring, brother!<br><br>Keep the shiney side up!<br><br>Aan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/urallousdreadsoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rallous Dreadsoul</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ele.uri.edu/~richg/rall.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 12:33:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2702.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ele.uri.edu/~richg/rallousface1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: To the bikers out there *longish*</span><hr size=1> No wipes this year ok Tel?